{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"311fb91f-f5d0-4d74-87c0-a993d2abb8aa","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `*.csproj`**\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`**\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`**\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\nThen run `dotnet restore` to pull updated packages. Check for any NuGet packages (e.g. `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*`, `Microsoft.Extensions.*`) that need their versions bumped to `11.x` as well.\n\nFinally, review the [.NET 11 breaking changes](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/core/compatibility/11.0) for any API or behavioral changes that affect your app.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"bc822098-9c09-4cfa-9519-6ed4386ea328","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward guidance question — no code to look at, no repo to modify. I'll provide concise instructions.","outputTokens":298,"requestId":"680F:B29EE:29C79A3:2DB1C3E:69FD29E8"},"id":"532ced0d-8754-4a20-b88d-d88c6950dacc","timestamp":"2026-05-08T00:10:22.813Z","parentId":"f424b819-ba39-4a9d-8153-7466ac4a0fa7"}
